<subsection xml:id="subsec-quadratic-equations" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Quadratic Equations</title>

    <p> A quadratic equation is an equation of the form <m>ax^2 + bx + c = 0</m>, where <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>, and <m>c</m> are constants, and <m>a \neq 0</m>. The solutions to a quadratic equation are called the roots of the equation. </p>
    
